<br>
FFA is a nasty way of saying the same thing, really.<br>
<br>
IF you show up to a mob and have the force to take it down... KILL IT.<br>
<br>
-Exceptions-<br>
<br>
If another group is obviously setting up (people are arriving, etc) and were there FIRST, back off. Let them take two tries at the mob. If they get smoked twice... then ask if you can kill it.<br>
<br>
If another group has just been wiped out there (and its obvious when this happens). Help them rez, give them another shot, then decide what to do from there.<br>
<br>
-Caveats-<br>
<br>
You NEED TO KNOW how much force it takes to kill a mob. If there are 12 60s on the island where Faydedar spawns... THAT FISH IS GONNA DIE... it is ample force and if you arrive second, i don't care how many 52nd level wizards you brought... they can kill it, back off and watch it. Its poetry, honest.<br>
<br>
If you're a 52-53+ guild... you need to understand that mobility equals success. If you get to OS and another guild is there with more than 20 people... you ask them if they are killing Trak... if they say yes, you move on. 10 minutes from EJ evac to OS, 2 minutes to talk... TWELVE minutes lost.<br>
<br>
If you're wasting an hour or two punching the clown... don't complain if an early bird eats your worm. It IS unfair for you to ask other people to postpone THEIR plans for you to take two hours to get anywhere.<br>
<br>
I hate to say 'I told you so' but... I did mention that we all were going to be 60th level together someday... you all need to understand that its not about being EQUAL, its about being FAIR and POLITE about killing things.<br>
<br>
Part of being polite is knowing when to back off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/28/02 2:04:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=416.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: i think you figured I had an opinion on this.</span><hr size=1> Don't like to get involved in these conversations but...<br>
